{ Show (Hide) Developer tab on Ribbon #excel-show-developer-tab

  In order to have the *record macro* button, the *Developer tab* must be first enabled (See also → Microsoft/Office/Excel/macro/recording[recording macros in Excel])

  This can be done in the → Windows/registry[registry] under
 `→ Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Office/application_version/Excel/Options` (value → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Office/application_version/Excel/Options#reg-excel-developer-tools[`DeveloperTools`]).

  Alternatively, the developer tools can also be enabled via the menu: File -> Options -> Customize Ribbon -> Check *Developer* box on right side.

  With → development/languages/VBA, the state of the developer tab can be queried or modified with → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Application#excel-application-showDevTools[`application.showDevTools`]:
code {
→ Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Application[application].→ Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Application/index#excel-application-showDevTools[showDevTools] = → development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes/boolean[true]
code }

}
